OL,3,CWoman fined after miscarriage calls
OL,4,Cnew baby loss certificates 'pointless'
OL,6,FTwo women from West Yorkshire say the
OL,7,Fnew do not go far enough.
OL,9,FSadie Hawkes, 34, miscarried before
OL,10,Fshe received a maternity exemption
OL,11,Fcertificate, which entitles women to
OL,12,Ffree medication. She had claimed a
OL,13,Ffree course of antibiotics before she
OL,14,Flost her baby.
OL,16,FThe NHS then sent her a letter saying
OL,17,Fshe owed them a #46.75 fine, as well
OL,18,Fas the #9.35 prescription charge,
OL,19,Fbecause she hadn't shown the
OL,20,Fcertificate.
